reviewText:
2003-2005 were not the best times for Sam. First, we had SS1 Xbox which I absolutely despised, then SS Next Encounter which in my humble opinion was an absolute disgrace and finally this, Serious Sam 2, which perhaps is in the middle ground.


Although the reasons why I dislike this game are many, a few of them are also subjective, so not everyone would concur with my standarts.
- the cartoony artstyle, the childish tone, the overused humour and the lack of gore made the game less compelling compared to the other Sam games;
- invisible walls plague the game;
- severe hand-holding;
- Painkiller-based arena battles. They're good in their own right, but this is Serious Sam, not Painkiller;
- cut-down exploration : SS2 likes feeding the player with resources considerably more than the other SS games do;
- too arcady : not as much as Next Encounter, but it still makes the impression that you're playing just for points. In SS1 the points weren't such a considerable part of the game.

Still, there are good things worth mentioning.
- the locales are varied and quite interesting, especially when they're in vein of SS1;
- the soundtrack is rather pleasing as well.
- good enemy variety;
- recaptures the very essence of Serious Sam - the 'Dancing with the enemies' type of gameplay.

All in all, I deem Serious Sam 2 to be the worst Serious Sam game out there, (I'm not talking about the spin-offs), albeit as a game on its own it's probably alright. SS1 and SS3 I find to be much more fun, much more compelling and just better games in general; I recommend those ones.
